  "text": "The actual implementation of this change of perspective is not evident from the point of view of traditional engineering techniques. Consequently we need to look for new sources of inspiration. Fortunately, animal sensory systems carry out a processing paradigm based on pathways that are built and reused to conform different functions. This optimally fits our requirement specification. In fact, we have previously used this same biological approach in order to construct an activity-dependent clustering method for organizing large arrays of artificial sensory receptors [CITATION_1] .",
